Package info.kgeorgiy.ja.sinitsyn.implementor

Class Implementor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.sinitsyn.implementor.Implementor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Impler, JarImpler
public class Implementor extends Object implements Impler, JarImpler
A tool to generate empty-classes that would inherit the given one.

This tool generates generic-supported classes without unchecked warnings.

Has two available methods implement(Class, Path) and implementJar(Class, Path) and three fields: PROJECT_NAME, IMPLEMENTATION_SUFFIX and date (the last one is only instance-accessible), that could be touched outside. Also could be run as self-sufficient code with method main(String[]).

    • imports

      private final Map<String,Class<?>> imports
      Map: class.name -> class. The whole list of found types that were used in class or interface for that this implementor generated implementation. Saves only that types which Class.getSimpleName() is different. For example:
      • java.util.List
      • java.awt.List
      For these two only one will be saved into the map. In order that it could be used by its simple name in generated code, while the other one will always be generated by its full name.

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: Impler
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • generateHeader

      private String generateHeader(Class<?> token) throws ImplerException

      Generates header for class like

      public class TestClassImpl extends TestClass

      Generates implementation-class header that extends or implements (weather token is class or interface) the given (token) one.

      If parent class is parametrized with generics, then the implementation would also be parametrized. And its parameter's bounds will be the same.

      public class Parent<E extends Number>
      public class Child<E extends Number> extends Parent<E>
      Parameters:
      token - type to be inherited
      Returns:
      string with generated package. If there is no package return empty string
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if preprocessingGenerics(Class) throws an exception

    • getTypeName

      private String getTypeName(Type type)
      Get name for the given type. This method do a bit different things for different input types:
      • Class - checks in imports map, then choose between Class.getSimpleName() and Class.getCanonicalName()
      • WildcardType - just Type.getTypeName()
      • TypeVariable - searches through generics map to get the full wrapper over the given type
      • GenericArrayType - recursive call for GenericArrayType.getGenericComponentType() plus []
      • ParameterizedType - get bounds for type anf generates result like this: "&lt;T extends AClass & BClass, E&gt;"
      Parameters:
      type - class to retrieve name from
      Returns:
      generated name for given type
      See Also:
      • Type
      • Class
      • WildcardType
      • TypeVariable
      • GenericArrayType
      • ParameterizedType

    • getGenerics

      private String getGenerics(TypeVariable<?>[] typeVariables)
      Method to get all bounds of given types. For each given type it will find its bounds and join them to one string separated by "&". After it concatenates all types to one string separated with commas.
      Parameters:
      typeVariables - array of generic variables
      Returns:
      string of concatenated generic types with their bounds (separated by comma). If type's bound is Object.class, it would return as if this type has no bounds.
      See Also:
      • TypeVariable

    • getBounds

      private List<String> getBounds(TypeVariable<?> typeVariable)
      Gets a list of all the bounds for typeArgument. For example:

      For &lt;T&gt; it will return:

      emptyList

      For &lt;T extends AType & BType&gt; it will return:

      • AType
      • BType
      Parameters:
      typeVariable - variable that could have bounds for it's type
      Returns:
      list of bounds. It ignores java.lang.Object as a type's bound. So, for &lt;T extends Object&gt; it will return emptyList
